<p></p>
<h3>What is the context of Gabon’s telecoms blackout?</h3>
<p>The internet shutdown has been imposed on election day as President Ali Bongo seeks to win a third seven-year term, furthering concerns over the democratic process in Gabon. It is likely the move will stifle transparency as the opposition hopes to challenge Bongo’s long-standing dominance. Internet service was previous cut in Gabon during the <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/evidence-of-gabon-full-internet-shutdown-coup-attempt-dQ8oo18n" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">2019 attempted coup</a>.</p>
<p>Gabon joins <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/whatsapp-and-social-media-restricted-in-zambia-on-election-day-18lpLY8a" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Zambia</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-shutdown-in-the-republic-of-the-congo-on-election-day-xAGR398z" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Congo</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/social-media-and-messaging-platforms-restricted-in-uganda-ahead-of-general-election-XB7aaO87" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Uganda</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-tanzania-on-eve-of-presidential-elections-oy9abny3" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Tanzania</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/guinea-blocks-social-media-on-eve-of-elections-ryb3rn87" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Guinea</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/social-media-disrupted-in-burundi-on-election-day-JBZLPY86" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Burundi</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/social-media-disrupted-in-togo-on-election-day-r8VWr4A5" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Togo</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/post-election-internet-shutdown-in-mauritania-following-widespread-mobile-disruptions-JA6zmeAQ" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Mauritania</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-blocked-in-benin-on-election-day-aAwqknyM" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Benin</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/facebook-and-whatsapp-restricted-in-cameroon-on-eve-of-election-results-YkArL1yj" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Cameroon</a>, <a href="https://netblocks.org/reports/mali-elections-marred-by-internet-disruptions-G3Anxqy2" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Mali</a> and other countries in the region that have faced internet shutdowns and social media restrictions during elections in recent years, limiting free expression and civic engagement at critical moments.</p>
